content.detailedDescription: I was at my old apartment complex. i went outside through my front door to have a smoke. i saw this very strange blinking light. i was staying in the same spot for a long time. i grabbed my phone and sat down in the chair i had on my front balcony. i started taking pictures / videos of what i thought was just a unexplainable blinking light. all i saw was a blinking light that seemed to be just hanging in the same spot. it would disappear and reappear in the same area for 2 hours. i could not stop looking at it because it just didn't move but was constantly blinking. bever stopped blinking but hovered in the same spot the entire time. it wasn't until i looked at the still pictures did i realize what it was. i was so amazed of what these pictures captured. it was some kind of spacecraft that seems to be having "car trouble" . it hovered in the same spot but turn around and showed differant views of the craft itself. it looked like an open faced sub sandwich.  i can see the solid outline of the craft which is the " bun of the sandwich". the  "ingredients" is where there was a constant bright white glowing light. in all of the pictures behind the craft there is always this faint blue glow. i think the white light is what powers it. i read about some kind of radiation that can be contained that gives off a blue glow like this did. it said it can be used for moving faster than the speed of light. if light passes through water it slows down. this white light is what it uses to be able to stop on a dime and switch directions then accelerate at the speed of light again. it can also be used to just hover in midair. i know what i saw was the most amazing and never seen before evidence of a real ufo. i watched snd took pictures for 2 hrs. i went inside just to get a drink. i laid down for just a minute and fell asleep. woke up after the sun came out and it was gone.
content.summary: It was just a strange blinking light that drew my attention to it. i started taking pictures. when i looked at the pictures is when i saw that it was a space craft.

content.detailedDescription: I just recently moved to anchorage, alaska...I am originally from san diego, california. i was headed to work the morning of december 1, 2015. i didn't start work until 9:00am, and had arrived shortly before 8:30am to the parking garage...I had some extra time...So i figured i'd get my phone out, send a snapchat to my friends back home, and show them just how dark it is in alaska at 830 in the morning. the stars looked unusually bright and stand out-ish to me for some reason that morning, i felt compelled to take a photo before starting the snapchat. when recording the snapchat, i am panning from the left, where you can see the moon in the top left corner, and moving to the right, away from the larger buildings, towards the water. i was watching my phone screen while i was recording, so i only saw one ufo dart across initially. it moved so fast, my eyes could hardly perceive it...It almost seemed like a bug that flew across my screen, and maybe i was just really tired. oh well, put the phone away and lets go to work! i didn't check my phone again until i was at work, and i replayed the video and immediately saw more ufos. i replayed the video over, and over, and over, trying to make sense of what i was seeing...And then i found i could zoom in while the video was playing, and it confirmed any doubts i had. upon zooming into the video, the ufos become more clear in definition and in pattern. to confirm i wasn't looking at light refractions either, one of the ufos even darts behind the top of the sheraton building, disappearing momentarily behind the building, and then reappearing again. i was the only witness to this event and even i did not believe what my own eyes had seen, it took me around 12 hours of watching the video to fully accept that i had just witnessed ufos, and weeks of re-watching it to come forth with it. when i looked at the very first photo i took, the photo before i recorded video, you can see multiple ufos hovering over downtown. the clearest definition of the ufos i found was in taking "screenshots" of the 9 second video clip and zooming in. the ufos appear to have clear, definitive patterns, shapes, and lines. they are glowing brighter than anything i have ever seen in the sky. i lost sight of the objects as soon as they were out of my iphone camera's line-of-sight.
content.summary: 8 ufos spotted hovering over downtown anchorage, then flew in triangle formations away from buildings towards water

content.detailedDescription:
This is the story my girlfriend told me less then 1 hour ago.

she and her sister live in chaiyaphum province north east thailand

about 20km from her house a large mountain range starts with mountains going up to almost 2km in hight.

today during night time she and her sister witnessed a glowing large object that appeared to be stationery in the air far above the mountains.

the object they described as being horn or v shaped which they couldn't really tell because it was so far away

they said it looked like it was on fire and the light even at that distance was very bright.

when they ran inside to get a camera phone the object was gone when they got back outside.

at that moment my girlfriend contacted me in the netherlands and she appeared to me as rather shocked of what she just saw.

i tried to figure out what she saw and that led me to believe they might have seen the giant v shaped ufo from the phoenix lights event years ago.

i looked for a picture on the internet and found one they said looks almost exactly the same as the object they seen.

the object either had redish fire color like lights or in my opinion it could have been moving through the atmosphere.

my girlfriend said that the object appeared not to move but considering the distance and angle of view it might have been moving up slowely without them noticing it.

the sighting happend today and so far we haven't figured out if anyone else seen it too.

sadly we do not have our own picture or video of the event but i can provide you with the picture i found on google which my girlfriend and her sister claim to be almost exactly the same thing they saw.
content.summary: Large horn/v shaped brilliant fire color ufo above mountain range 20km away

content.detailedDescription: I was standing over my kitchen sink looking east while washing a glass,i noticed 5 bright orbed shaped objects hovering and changing from orange to red and then white.Objects then moved horizoally back and forth for approximately 10 mins.Then hovered a few minutes, then shot straight up at an incredible speed and disappeared. at first i was stunned and just stood there trying to take understand what i just saw.I know what i saw was real,i haven't told anyone about this not sure what i should do about that. i also experienced a ufo while in the usaf by the gulf of mexico on several occasions i notified base authority's which at that point classified what i saw ss top secret and i received top secret clearance as well after background check. at that point my work was kept top secret along with my new position with the usaf.Details not available after that point. that was in 1976 at kessler air force base bilox mississippi. this episode brought back uncomfortable feelings. was stunned to see this again,all i can say at this time. world is changing rapidly and the majority of people have no clue what is going on behind the scenes....No evidence to support this as of now may possibly send in evidence of drawing but not now.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Saw ufo out kitchen window to the east 5 orbs hovering moving side to side do

content.detailedDescription: Went to van for my morning ciggarette before i wake kids up for school and on way to van which was approx 40 ft from back door i looked up at sky like always do ( lived in town for long time and couldnt see many stars there) and noticed some stars just started disapearing  it caught me off guard so i looked better and saw a greyish smooth metal object right in front of me approx 80 ft away moveing slowly towards the left and about 3 seconds after i noticed it a blue neon like triangle lit up and with in 2 seconds of the light illuminateing it shot just a little bit towards left from being straight up and was gone dont recall any sound .. i have a bass boat with a decent amount of old blood on the seat and i believe it had the crafts attention at the time that i first stepped out the back door that morning.. also i believe only reason i saw it before it dissapeared was that there are power lines just on other side of bass boat about 10' away from it ..
content.summary: Went out for ciggarette from van noticed stars disapearing  looked closer saw craft move a bit horizontal to ground  saw blue triangle light up and in 2seconds it dissapeared from sight

content.detailedDescription:
Driving west on fred waring in palm desert, i saw two oval-shaped objects in the clear sky. they were headed relatively fast towards west, seemed to be quite high up in the air, and i couldn’t hear any sound. (i was in a car so that may have been the reason.) the two objects were close to each other and kept the same distance and configuration. they were both identical in appearance: oval, dark in color, somewhat metallic looking. at the time, i and the driver of the car had no idea what they may be. they didn’t look like anything i had seen before, and i couldn’t think of anything known they could be. they went too fast for being a balloon. they were definitely not birds. it was daylight so they were not obviously planets or meteors. they were not civilian drones since they went fast and continued over the mountains. they did not have the shape of any airplane i have seen.

thinking back now, it is possible that they were two helicopters and we didn’t see the rotors or any of the things normally protruding from helicopters. it’s possible, but it does seem unlikely that we wouldn’t have seen any of those things and the perfect oval shape of both objects didn’t fit the shape of helicopters i have seen. it is possible that they were military drones flying in perfect formation and with no visible or audible form of propulsion. i don’t know if military drones comes in a perfectly oval shape. it was certainly an odd sight.
content.summary: Two oval shape objects heading west.

content.detailedDescription:
I live on a bluff over the kansas river facing south. i was making a video using my dji phantom 3 quadcopter. i flew south over the river and over a lake formed by a sand and gravel pit then turned north and flew back over my house. i cut out some of the video, added some music and showed the video to friends. no-one  noticed anything unusual. later as i was examining the video to see how i could make another one that would be better i noticed a fast moving object heading almost straight at me from 12 o'clock ending a short distance to my left at 9 o'clock. this object appeared white in color and flew a straight line while in the video. the object appeared extremely fast moving. this observation deeply concerned me and i showed it to my wife and a close friend that i have a great respect for to get their opinion. both stated that it looked very unusual to them. my friend asked "what the he** was that?" 

the object appears in the video over the far side of the lake. the lake is right at 700 yards across at that point. i was shooting at 30 frames per second and the object is in view for 6 frames. adding a 7th frames to ensure it was past the near shoreline i calculate that it took 0.233 seconds to travel the 2100 feet. if my math is correct that means it was traveling at approximately 9,068 mph or 11.92 mach.

i am including a clip of the video that shows the encounter and i cut the frame out where the object was closest to me. there is a screen shot of that plus i used filters in photoshop that helps remove blur from an object (high pass and unsharp mask). those are also included.

there were white seagulls flying around the lake at the time, but in the video, as well as physical observations since, i see no behavior that resembles this observation.
content.summary: Fast moving object caught on video

content.detailedDescription: Was outside looking at stars because it was so clear tonight    suddenly a large bright horseshoe shaped object appeared in se horizon traveling  very slowly  seemingly low across sky without sound towards the west.  it was much larger than any star at least 20x larger than any  stars visible tonight.   it had 2 distinct tails  as long as the main body which were outlined in black against extremely bright white surface. the edge was visible against the night sky.  seemed odd.  while watching it just suddenly disappeared.  nothing.  totally gone.   from a really large and bright object  it looked like it was beginning to descend then paused for a couple seconds and seemed to tilt angle upward ascending a second or so   then disappearing into nothing.  vanished! it was as though the lights were just turned off.  from totally bright and visible to gone!  i didn't know what to think.  i have never seen a shooting star that large or moving that slow.  it seemed to move at the speed you see with helicopters but it was not a helicopter!:
content.flightPath: Stationary,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Slow moving shaped like horseshoe black outline border both sides with bright light  vanished instantaneously

content.detailedDescription: It was late summer in 1956. i was 8years old. i was sitting on the back porch after everyone else went inside. i noticed what looked like a flame moving across the sky, which looked really cool. as i watched the flame it moved in a straight line from my right to my left. as the flame was straight out in front of me i saw what looked like a person in the front of the flame, who i waved at and he waved back. the flame continued to move to my left. as it got a little past me the flame then shot straight up into the air, which i thought was pretty cool. when i went in the house and told my dad and uncle about what i saw, they told me it was swamp gas. being 8 years old what did i know. however that night while my brother and i were sleeping on the sofa bed, something woke us up. at that time there was a person standing next to the sofa bed. as this scared me and my brother, i stood up on the sofa bed which made me about 6 feet tall, which would have made the person about 7 or 8 feet tall,  i still had to look up at the person. at that time not knowing who this was i told my brother to run to our dad's bedroom and i followed him out of the room. i could not see the person's face as he was wearing a hooded robe  that covered his face. i have never had another encounter. but i have been looking for ufo's ever since. my brother did not see the flame, but he did see the person in the room.
content.summary: Saw what looked like a flame that had a shadow of a person toward the front of the flame

content.detailedDescription:
Backstory:  two or three nights prior to the incident, my friend (i'll call her "a") and i drove to pick up her niece from her boyfriend's house.  i drove my car.  we picked up the niece and on the way home, "a" suggested we take another back road that was a shorter route.  this particular route was done a lonely country road through a very rural farming community.  we approached a railroad crossing and just before i drove over the tracks, i saw the silhouette of an airplane flying directly above the treetops in front of us.  i stopped at the stop sign to watch what i assumed was a military issued plane** flying at an alarmingly low altitude (barely above the treetops). the strangest thing was, the plane's engines weren't running--there was no sound.  i turned off the car engine and poked my head out the window to better be able to hear and i was really confused as to how this military plane** could possibly be flying so low without any engines running and not crash?  we all watched the plane as it flew over a patch of pine woods, until we could no longer see it.  we all thought it was strange, but nonetheless, we didn't dwell on it and we went on with the ride home without thinking any more of it.

**it should be noted parenthetically that we didn't actually see any identifiable markings on the plane that would authenticate it as being a u.S. military aircraft.  i make that assumption based on the shape of the plane being consistent with other u.S. military aircraft and its dark color.

two or three days later:  my friend "a" and i are, again, in my car.  we were heading out of town to look for jobs.  we decided to take a back road through the woods and farmsteads, since it would connect us quicker to the highway than the normally traveled route (not the same road from a few nights earlier, but around the same area).  we'd used this road before with no incident.  it was a perfectly clear day, around 1:00pm or 1:30pm and the weather was warm and bright.  we were both very eager to apply for jobs that day.  
the road we traveled was a dirt road (red clay) that cut through some very isolated terrain.  to our left was a single farm house and an expansive corn field and to our right was a pine forest.  we had only been driving this part of the road for about four minutes (we'd just passed the farm house) when i saw what looked like the same military plane flying out from over the pine woods to our right.  it was again flying just a few hundred feet above the tree tops with no sound.  this time, i immediately stopped the car, shut off the engine and we both exited the car and stood in the middle of the road, in the middle of the day, to see just what the hell was going on.  again, we were so perplexed as to how this plane could just glide smoothly without any engines running and manage to stay at the same altitude??  the plane glided (like a hang glider) over the outer edge of the pine woods, along the edge of the road, headed in our direction.  as we stood and watched, i barely noticed a flash of white somewhere over the pine wood, just on the other side of the plane.  i didn't give it any attention because i was so transfixed on this plane with strange flying habits.  "a" suddenly asked, "what is that thing?", to which i dismissively replied, "it's probably a bird" (there were large white crane-like birds in the area).  my friend shouts, "that's not a f*cking bird!"  
i take my eyes off the plane to take a look at the white object (i was a little irritated that she was distracting me, while i'm trying to figure out what this plane is doing).  just as the plane veers back over the pine wood, this "thing" flies from over the tree tops, directly beneath the plane and out into the clear, right above us.  the plane has now disappeared over the tree tops and out of sight and we never saw it, again.  it was (this is the best i can describe it) a white object that was shaped like a dumbell or a peanut that was turned on its side, horizontally.  it moved at a slow, but steady pace and in a straight line, from right to left.  since it flew just below the plane, i could tell easily, that it was about the size of a standard yellow school bus (approximately 30-35 feet long).  it had no markings, no windows, no seams, no rivets, no hatches, no engines or exhaust--nothing--just a solid object, colored white, that was low enough that its appearance could be easily determined.  as we watched (neither of us spoke for the next ten minutes), the object changed from a solid white to silver (like mercury) and reflections of the pine trees and corn field could be seen on its surface!!!  after a few moments, the object (still moving steadily, but painfully slow) "changed color" again, this time, however, it turned "opalescent" and seemed to shimmer in hues of pastel pink, blue and white.  that's when it became completely transparent, like glass, and only a faint outline could be seen.  it bears repeating that this was a perfectly clear day with not even a single cloud in the sky--not one.  the object "shimmered" back into view and was again, opalescent and then, silver colored, then white, again.  this pattern repeated itself for the duration of the sighting.  the object has now made its way across the dirt road and over the vast corn field.  all of a sudden, from the left of the sky, there was a white "cloud" (i use the term loosely, because while it had the same color and texture as a white cloud, it was smooth and almost perfectly spherical, like a cotton ball.  the cloud seemed to literally appear out of nowhere.  the object, still "changing color", approached the "cloud" and entered it.  the cloud and the object were roughly the same size, the "cloud" being only slightly bigger as to barely accommodate the size of the object flying into it.  the object never emerged from the "cloud" and within a few seconds, the "cloud" itself just faded out of existence, as though it was never there.  the sky was once again empty, clear and blue.  i snapped out of the slack-jawed trance i seemed to be in and immediately knelt down and drew the peanut shaped object i witnessed, in the dirt, with my finger.  my friend, now crying, said, "that's what i saw, too".  from the time we saw the plane and stopped the car, until the time the object and the "cloud" disappeared was approximately ten minutes.
we were both effectively scared and confused by what we saw and at the idea that whoever was flying the military plane had to have seen that we were watching this phenomena unfold and they might come back for us, having seen something we weren't supposed to.  we got back in the car and i drove her back home.  i, too, went back home and didn't leave my house again for almost a week.  during this time, i told my aunt about the incident, just in case i suddenly went missing.  please understand, that i'm not a conspiracy theorist, nor am i a paranoid person.  in fact, i would normally condescend those that claim to have encounters with ufos or the "men in black".  after this, however, i have respect for those people. i won't claim that what i saw was extraterrestrial because i don't have enough information to come to that conclusion.  it could've been some secret military weapon or experimental aircraft, for all i know.  i do know that whatever we saw, it was not normal and i'm pretty sure it was none of our business.  i was thirty years old that summer and my friend was twenty-five.

i no longer live in south carolina, but i am still connected to this young lady via facebook and about once a year, i send her a message asking her to remind me that i'm not insane and that we really saw what we saw.  she always replies that, yes, we did see it and that no one believes her when she tells the story.  

unfortunately, we did not have a camera to take pictures or video.  this occurred in 2008, before the advent of the smart phone.  i can't prove to anyone else that what we saw was real, but i know it happened and so does the young lady, "a".  the events transpired as described, without any embellishments or assumptions.  what you've read is how it happened.  i'm willing to take a polygraph.
content.summary: Dumbell shaped object flew horizontally overhead, changing color and momentarily fading in and out of view before entering a small, unnaturally shaped "cloud", never exiting.

content.detailedDescription: I was out on my front porch of my home having a cigarette.  i noticed the natural light outside around sunset almost felt artificial or surreal. i also noticed that the clouds were moving particularly fast.  as i looked over the mountain just south west of my home i noticed three funnel shaped clouds coming up from behind the mountain.  now they looked like the trails that some aircraft leave, but they were vertical in nature and there were no planes/jets in the area.  as i followed the trail upward i noticed that the three trails/funnels merged together around a disc like shape that seemed to be ascending into the sky. i snapped some photos as i think that i may have just witnessed a craft taking off.  the wind was blowing hard and the other cloud blew on, but the funnels and disc shaped remained after. over the course of about 20 minutes the shape slowly became transparent and faded from view.
content.summary: Triple funnel clouds rising from behind mountain and shrouding disc like shape in clouds

content.detailedDescription:
I went outside first thing this morning. after sitting outside for a few minutes, i looked west at the fog covering the hillside. then, there was a bright, almost blinding light that made my eyes tear up; i mean tears rolling down my face. the object did not move. it appeared to be in front of the heavy fog. it appeared to be above the hill and slightly in front of the hill. after snapping a few pictures, it appeared to dim. it had a translucence to it. i looked down at my camera to make sure i had gotten the shot, looked up, and it was gone. after having examined the pictures i took, the pictures effectively portray exactly how the object looked to my eyes. the top of the object is completely dome shaped. the bottom is jagged as if there were trees in front of the object. behind that hill, there is a cluster of trees that could have caused this effect, but it would mean that there was an object behind the trees, bright enough to cut through the heavy, morning fog. in the pictures, the sun is clearly visible to the left of the object. the light that the object emitted looked to be the same or similar to the sun, but it could not have been a reflection because the sun was behind and to the left of the object. it also does not and did not, appear to be a break in the fog. it was clearly in front of the heavy fog. i've lived high up in the rocky mountains for quite some time now, and i have seen my fair share of weird "light tricks" caused by ice particles in the atmosphere -- i've never seen anything quite like this. if there is a scientific explanation for this, i would love to hear it...Although the author in me wants to think it was a glitch in a cloaking device, (har, har). 

i've included the original unaltered images as well as copies of the same images that i inverted. 

thank you!
content.summary: Bright object in the western sky at sunrise.

content.detailedDescription: I was looking out my window looking at the sky. then i saw a light blue u-shaped light zoom past in the sky. it looked like it was going upwards. it was not an airplane because an airplane at the altitude wouldn't look like that and also an airplane doesn't it fly that fast. it flew very very fast. it flew straight then disappeared. just like that. it made me feel scared and happy.
content.summary: I was staring out my window. the u shaped light passed the sky very fast.

content.detailedDescription: At approximately 8:20 pm i was traveling eastward on nys rt 31 between clay and cicero ny. i observed two orange lights traveling parallel to the road. the lights seemed low, definately beneath the cloud cover. i pulled my car over to watch. the lights passed over my car, then turned north abruptly. they were visible for about 30 seconds after their course change and then disappeared.
content.summary: Observed orange lights moving from e to w then turned abruptly and disappeared.

content.detailedDescription: Suddenly noticed outside when i was nonchalantly looking out window around 2:30am-3am. watched it for about 15 minutes wondering what it was. small object with blinking white, green and red lights. it was circling the area for about an hour i believe. didn't look like a helicopter. thought it was a drone, but what would a person be doing at 3am flying a drone in large circles for an hour? made no sense. i have no idea what it is.
content.distance: 501 Feet - 1 Mile, Over 1 Mile, Unknown, N/A
content.summary: Small object circling area. blinking white, green, and red lights.

content.detailedDescription: Saturday 12 of december 2015, we were having a relaxing time at home in the back yard. the kids were swimming in the pool, at around 4pm i started the fire for the braai and was on my way back into the house. the kids started scramming very excitedly at me to look at the sky “look there, daddy look there” they shouted, i turned and saw in a easterly direction a orange ball of light in the sky descending, at first i thought it was a plane as the johannesburg international airport is in that direction,but it was too close to be from the airport it then stopped for about a minute, then moved slowly to the left, it stopped again in mid-air and hovered, after about 3-4 mins it ascended straight up into the air at amazing speed until it was out of sight. my wife, son and nephew also saw the light and its actions. i felt very confused about what i saw and took me sometime to decide to make this report, ive seen how people get treat when they report things like this.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Orange ufo seen near johannesburg international airport

content.detailedDescription: Me and my families were leaving ranco cordova and as we weregetting onto the freeway we noticed a triangular craft off in the distance. in a few seconds,as we got into the highway, the object had completely changed directions and was heading in our path. all of a sudden it was about 50 ft. above our car and it went off in the distance heading west when all of a sudden it sped up to incredible speeds and left.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: It was a dark triangular object.

content.detailedDescription: In my backyard with dogs looking up at the stars and saw one a little different colored a little more pinkish. standing still looking it moves in counterclockwise circles real small. if you weren't looking at it you would  not notice it. it you look at something else close but stationary keeping it in periphial vision it moves and the stationary thing in your sight does not. it looked like it was just having fun. it is still there. looks like another one is up there with it but far from it. more west same brightness, same motions color etc.I smiled watching it and texted the mufon investigator in my region. from orions belt alnitak look east the closest pinkish "star". watch it move in circles just one sometimes two consectively, then it will go eastward and back once or twice. note the motions are very small but big enough to see if you really look.
content.summary: Looks like a pinkish star but if you watch it moves in small and larger circles sometimes sideways. its just having fun
